Description: Great sound and extremely comfortable feel. Hagstrom Sweden is a pioneer of electric guitars known for for excellence in design & build. This D2H Deluxe model has a lot of unexpected quality in the details that make this axe desirable. Highly recommended! The construction style is very similar to a Fender FMT Tele with better balance. I find the best things to be the tuning stability (graphite nut, stout 18-1 tuners, solid H-truss rod, and bolt-down block tailpiece instead of the typical "goal-post" studs), the weight balance, natural-feeling neck & frets, and the great pickups & tone. The carved maple top is pewter color with silver mist (glows nicely under stage lights), and transparent brown neck & back. Alnico V pickups keep even tone from low to high volumes (treble-bleed is not a problem like most) and behave beautifully under high sound pressure. The sustain is exactly what you would expect from better slab mahogany build. This is tour ready. I use light flat wound strings, and it comes with a sturdy Les Paul-style case in good condition: no tears or bad hardware. I use USPS Priority Mail and FEDEX. Please send any questions or combined shipping invoice requests, and THANKS, EVERYONE! Any offers may be refused for security reasons.
